This paper is about training acoustic models for German Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) using open source tools. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and speech recognition. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.SD (Software Engineering) another likely category. The paper also discusses the performance of the model, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Signal Processing). Finally, the paper discusses the availability and licensing of the data used, which could also fall under cs.SD.
